value: Breeds in western North America from British Columbia to California and from Lake Winnipeg to southern Nova Scotia, south to Texas, Florida and Cuba. Winters in the southern half of its breeding area.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Inland waters near woodland, such as swamps, flooded forest, ponds, marshes, and along slow-moving streams and rivers, where nesting in holes in trees and bird boxes; winters mainly on fresh-water marshes, ponds, streams, and occasionally brackish marshes and estuaries.
fresh ponds, lakes, slow rivers in well-wooded & more open country
